/*
Set-Based Hashing

Problem 1 – Longest Consecutive Sequence

Given an integer array nums, find the length of the longest sequence of consecutive numbers.
Sequence must be made of numbers that appear anywhere in the array (not necessarily contiguous).




    public int longestConsecutive(int[] nums) {
        Set<Integer> hash = new HashSet<>();
        int maxlen = 0;
        for(int x:nums){
            hash.add(x);
        }
        for(int x : hash){
            if(!hash.contains(x-1)){
                int curr = x;
                int len = 1;
                while(hash.contains(curr + 1)){
                    curr++;
                    len++;
                }
                maxlen = Math.max(maxlen,len);
            }
        }
        return maxlen;
    }




    Problem 2 — Check if Array Has Unique Elements (Using HashSet)

    Given an array, check if all elements are unique or not.
Agar koi element repeat hota mil jaye → return false
Agar sab unique → return true


public boolean containsDuplicate(int[] nums) {
        HashSet<Integer> result = new HashSet<>();
        for(int x: nums){
           
            if(result.contains(x)){
                return true;
            }
             result.add(x);
        }
        return false;
    }




    Next Problem (Module–4) → “Intersection of Two Arrays

    public int[] intersection(int[] nums1, int[] nums2) {
        Set<Integer> hash = new HashSet<>();
        Set<Integer> ans = new HashSet<>();
        for(int x: nums1){
            hash.add(x);
        }
        for(int x:nums2){
            if(hash.contains(x)){
                ans.add(x);
            }
        }
        return ans.stream().mapToInt(Integer::intValue).toArray();
    }

    Problem 4 - Union of two arrays.

    public static ArrayList<Integer> findUnion(int[] a, int[] b) {
        Set<Integer> hash = new HashSet<>();
        for(int x:a){
            hash.add(x);
        }
        for(int x:b){
            hash.add(x);
        }
         return new ArrayList<>(hash);
    }

    In this problem learn the way to return set in arraylist.
*/